Class MultiMIFARE

java.lang.Object
  com.nxp.id.jcopx.MultiMIFARE

public class MultiMIFARE
extends java.lang.Object

MultiMIFARE is a JCOP proprietary extension containing the API to the Multi MIFARE Emulation Framework.

getDefaultActivationParameters

public static final void getDefaultActivationParameters(byte[] resultArray,
                                                        short resultArrayOffset)
Returns the JCOP default activation parameters that are used in case JCOP does the activation.
Data structure:
ATQA0 ATQA1 SAK_Incomplete SAK_Complete UIDOption
UID00 UID01 UID02 UID03
UID04 UID05 UID06 UID07 UID08 UID09 ATS00 ATS01
ATS02 ATS03 ATS04 ATS05 ATS06 ATS07 ATS08 ATS09
ATS10 ATS11 ATS12 ATS13 ATS14 ATS15 ATS16 ATS17
ATS18 ATS19

Parameters:
resultArray - array to store the result in (minimum size: 35 byte)
resultArrayOffset - offset in resultArray

setActivationParameters

public static final short setActivationParameters(short VCx,
                                                  byte UIDOption,
                                                  short ATQA,
                                                  byte SAK_InComplete,
                                                  byte SAK_Complete,
                                                  byte DESFireDecisionOption,
                                                  byte[] ATS,
                                                  short ATSOffset,
                                                  short ATSLength,
                                                  byte[] password,
                                                  short passwordOffset,
                                                  short passwordLength)
Sets activation parameters as of the next activation.
In case this function has not been called or the Virtual Card is deactivated, JCOP will use factory default activation parameters (secrow for UID and fabkey for ATQA and SAK_Complete & SAK_Incomplete and PHEAP for ATS).

Parameters:
VCx - Virtual Card ID
UIDOption - interpreted by JCOP, UID is extracted (if necessary) by calling the emulation framework with the password.
Following UID options are allowed:
0000_0001B - Use Random UID (generated by the framework)
0000_0010B - Use 7-byte UID stored in P5 Security Row
0000_0100B - Use 4-byte FnUID derived from UID in P5 Security Row
0000_1000B - Use Virtual Card UID of swapped in Virtual Card
ATQA - ATQA as defined in ISO14443 (byte order ATQA0, ATQA1)
SAK_InComplete - SAK Incomplete as defined in ISO14443
SAK_Complete - SAK Complete as defined in ISO14443
DESFireDecisionOption - defines criteria on how to route the first received I-block to MF DESFire card
ATS - ATS string array
ATSOffset - offset in the array ATS
ATSLength - length of the array ATS
password - The password is always checked. In case password is wrong, the activation will be done with the default parameters of JCOP.
passwordOffset - offset in array password
passwordLength - length of the password
Returns:
ConstantX.NX_TRUE16 if operation was successful, ConstantX.NX_FALSE16 otherwise
Throws:
JCOPXException - with the following reason codes:
  • JCOPXException.MMF_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if Multi MIFARE is not enabled
  • coded as [0x03 | return value from Mifare OS call]

vCardAdmin

public static final byte vCardAdmin(byte subFunction,
                                    byte[] parameter,
                                    short parameterOffset,
                                    short parameterLength,
                                    byte[] result,
                                    short resultOffset,
                                    short resultLength)
Calls the Multi MIFARE emulation framework directly.
In case this method leads to a card status not equal "activated", the default activation parameters of JCOP are used for the next activation.

Parameters:
subFunction - subfunction to call from the remote interface
parameter - array copied to a temporary buffer, containing memory window that is mapped to Multi MIFARE
parameterOffset - offset into the array parameter, starting position for memory window that is mapped to Multi MIFARE
parameterLength - is the size of the memory window within array parameter that is mapped to Multi MIFARE
result - contains the result of the Multi MIFARE emulation execution
resultOffset - offset into the array result
resultLength - size of the array result
Returns:
exit code of the Multi MIFARE emulation
Throws:
JCOPXException - with the following reason codes:
  • JCOPXException.MMF_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if Multi MIFARE is not enabled
See Also:
"SmartMX CVEC interface documentation (for parameter setting regarding subfunctions)"

vCardSwapOutNext

public static final short vCardSwapOutNext(short VCx,
                                           byte[] swapOutData,
                                           short swapOutDataOffset,
                                           short swapOutDataLength)
Performance optimized swapOut.
This command triggers the next command to swap out as many data blocks as fit into the swapOutData array. The initiation and finalization of the swapping process needs to be done using the method vCardAdmin(byte, byte[], short, short, byte[], short, short)

Parameters:
VCx - Virtual Card ID
swapOutData - the array that shall contain all retrieved data
swapOutDataOffset - the offset in array swapOutData
swapOutDataLength - the number of bytes that are allowed to be swapped out at most
Returns:
number of bytes that were swapped out. The returned length equal 0 means that Virtual Card image has been swapped out and the operation shall be completed by vCardAdmin(byte, byte[], short, short, byte[], short, short) with subfunction MMF_SWAPOUT_VC and parameter MMF_SWAPOUT_OPTION_FINAL.
Throws:
JCOPXException - with the following reason codes:
  • JCOPXException.MMF_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if Multi MIFARE is not enabled
  • coded as [0x03 | return value from Mifare OS call]

vCardSwapInNext

public static final byte vCardSwapInNext(short VCx,
                                         byte[] swapInData,
                                         short swapInDataOffset,
                                         short swapInDataLength)
Performance optimized swapIn.
This command triggers the next command of the emulation only. The initiation of the swapping process needs to be done using the method vCardAdmin(byte, byte[], short, short, byte[], short, short)

Parameters:
VCx - Virtual Card ID
swapInData - the array that contains the Virtual Card image data
swapInDataOffset - the offset in array swapInData
swapInDataLength - the number of bytes of Virtual Card image to be swapped in
Returns:
MMF_OK_MORE_DATA if swap in was successful and next data chunk expected. MMF_OK if last data chunk successfully swapped in.
Throws:
JCOPXException - with the following reason codes:
  • JCOPXException.MMF_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if Multi MIFARE is not enabled
  • coded as [0x03 | return value from Mifare OS call]
